cutPowerDomainByOverlaps(25.10)                cutPowerDomainByOverlaps(25.10)

Name
       cutPowerDomainByOverlaps  -  When you floorplan one power domain (inner
       domain) completely inside the other power domain  (outer  domain),  use
       this command to cut the outer domain as a hollow or donut shape

Syntax
       cutPowerDomainByOverlaps

       <powerDomainName>

       [-help]

       When  you  floorplan  one power domain (inner domain) completely inside
       the other power domain (outer domain), use  this  command  to  cut  the
       outer domain as a hollow or donut shape.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each cutPowerDomainByOverlaps parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man cutPowerDomainByOverlaps.

       <powerDomainName>
              Specifies  the  outer power domain where the nested power domain
              will reside.

Examples
       Here is an example of using this command. In this  example,  the  power
       domains,  PD1  and  PD2, are defined in the power intent file, and then
       the bounding box for each domain is specified:

       modifyPowerDomainAttr PD1 -box llx lly urx usy

        modifyPowerDomainAttr PD2 -box llx lly urs usy

        ....

       Note: The bounding box for PD2  must  lie  completely  within  the  PD1
       bounding box.

       Designate PD1 as the hollow power domain:

       cutPowerDomainByOverlaps PD1

       Instances in PD1 will not be placed within PD2.

